function Start(idActor, fRange, idActorDetector)

-- Drop a marker at the location the player is coming from.
-- This sets the escape direction for the NPC.
	idEscapeLoc = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(S_ACTOR_MARKER_LOCATION, idActor, false, 0,0)
	
end

function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)
	
-- Sets a damage cap on the elite so it can't die until the hunter kills it.
	Hydra.ActorSetDamageCap(idActorSpawned, 0.25)
	
end

function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)
	
-- Increment the number of normals killed.		
	N_NORMAL_KILLED = N_NORMAL_KILLED + 1	

-- For every 5 normal monsters killed spawn the special elite and reset the counter.		
	if N_NORMAL_KILLED >= 5 and bEliteCanSpawn == true then
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(ID_ELITE_SPAWNER) then
			Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(ID_ELITE_SPAWNER)
			bEliteCanSpawn = false
		end
		N_NORMAL_KILLED = 0
	end	
		
end

function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)

-- Increment the number of elites killed		
	N_ELITE_KILLED = N_ELITE_KILLED + 1	
	bEliteCanSpawn = true
	
-- Spawn a specific monster near the player in response to the elite dying
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(ID_ELITE_DEAD_SPAWN) then
			Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(ID_ELITE_DEAD_SPAWN)
		end

-- After the first elite dies add more monsters		
	if 	N_ELITE_KILLED == 1 then
		for i, idWave02Spawn in ipairs(T_WAVE02) do
			if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idWave02Spawn) then
				Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idWave02Spawn, false)
			end
		end
		Hydra.ActorPlaySimpleConversation(S_CONVERSATION_NORMALDEFEATED, ID_NPC_DRUID)
		
	-- After more elites die add even more monsters	
	elseif N_ELITE_KILLED == 2 then
		for i, idWave03Spawn in ipairs(T_WAVE03) do
			if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idWave03Spawn) then
				Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idWave03Spawn, false)
			end
		end
	end
		
end
